parLastPScvTime.name: parLastPScvTime
parLastPScvTime.description: Most recent date and time at which planned scavenging took place. Planned scavenging happens at intervals specified in the registry. Scavenging involves changing owned non-refreshed entries to the released state. Further, replicas may be changed to tombstones, tombstones maye be deleted and revalidation of old replicas may take place

parLastATScvTime.name: parLastATScvTime
parLastATScvTime.description: Most recent data and time at which scavenging as a result of administrative action took place

parLastTombScvTime.name: parLastTombScvTime
parLastTombScvTime.description: Most recent data and time at which replica tombstone scavenging took place

parLastVerifyScvTime.name: parLastVerifyScvTime
parLastVerifyScvTime.description: Most recent data and time at which revalidation of old active replicas took place

parLastPRplTime.name: parLastPRplTime
parLastPRplTime.description: Most recent data and time at which planned replication took place. Planned replication happens at intervals specified in the registry

parLastATRplTime.name: parLastATRplTime
parLastATRplTime.description: Most recent data and time at which administrator triggered replication took place.

parLastNTRplTime.name: parLastNTRplTime
parLastNTRplTime.description: Most recent data and time at which network triggered replication took place. Network triggered replication happens as a result of an update notification message from a remote WINS

parLastACTRplTime.name: parLastACTRplTime
parLastACTRplTime.description: Most recent data and time at which address change triggered replication took place. Address change triggered replication happens when the address of an owned name changes due to a new registration

parLastInitDbTime.name: parLastInitDbTime
parLastInitDbTime.description: Most recent data and time at which the local database was populated statically from one or more data files

parLastCounterResetTime.name: parLastCounterResetTime
parLastCounterResetTime.description: Most recent data and time at which the local counters were initialized to zero

parWinsTotalNoOfReg.name: parWinsTotalNoOfReg
parWinsTotalNoOfReg.description: This variable indicates the number of registrations received

parWinsTotalNoOfQueries.name: parWinsTotalNoOfQueries
parWinsTotalNoOfQueries.description: This variable indicates the number of queries received

parWinsTotalNoOfRel.name: parWinsTotalNoOfRel
parWinsTotalNoOfRel.description: This variable indicates the number of releases received

parWinsTotalNoOfSuccRel.name: parWinsTotalNoOfSuccRel
parWinsTotalNoOfSuccRel.description: This variable indicates the number of releases that succeeded

parWinsTotalNoOfFailRel.name: parWinsTotalNoOfFailRel
parWinsTotalNoOfFailRel.description: This variable indicates the number of releases that failed

parWinsTotalNoOfSuccQueries.name: parWinsTotalNoOfSuccQueries
parWinsTotalNoOfSuccQueries.description: This variable indicates the number of queries that succeeded

parWinsTotalNoOfFailQueries.name: parWinsTotalNoOfFailQueries
parWinsTotalNoOfFailQueries.description: This variable indicates the number of queries that failed

parRefreshInterval.name: parRefreshInterval
parRefreshInterval.description: This variable indicates the refresh interval. Unit is in milliseconds

parTombstoneInterval.name: parTombstoneInterval
parTombstoneInterval.description: This variable indicates the tombstone interval, Unit is in milliseconds

parTombstoneTimeout.name: parTombstoneTimeout
parTombstoneTimeout.description: This variable indicates the tombstone timeout. Unit is in milliseconds

parVerifyInterval.name: parVerifyInterval
parVerifyInterval.description: This variable indicates the verify interval Unit is in milliseconds.

parVersCounterStartValLowWord.name: parVersCounterStartValLowWord
parVersCounterStartValLowWord.description: This variable indicates the low word of the version counter that WINS should start with

parVersCounterStartValHighWord.name: parVersCounterStartValHighWord
parVersCounterStartValHighWord.description: This variable indicates the High word of the version counter that WINS should start with

parRplOnlyWCnfPnrs.name: parRplOnlyWCnfPnrs
parRplOnlyWCnfPnrs.description: This variable indicates whether or not replication should be done with non-configures pnrs. If not set to zero, replication will be done only with partners listed in the registry (except when an update notification comes in)

parStaticDataInit.name: parStaticDataInit
parStaticDataInit.description: This variable indicates whether Static data should be read in at initialization and reconfiguration time. Update of any mib variable in the parameters group constitutes reconfigurations

parLogFlag.name: parLogFlag
parLogFlag.description: This variable indicates whether logging should be done. Default behaviour is to do logging

parLogFileName.name: parLogFileName
parLogFileName.description: This variable gives the path to the log file

parBackupDirPath.name: parBackupDirPath
parBackupDirPath.description: This variable gives the path to the backup dir

parDoBackupOnTerm.name: parDoBackupOnTerm
parDoBackupOnTerm.description: This variable specifies whether WINS should do backup on termination. Setting it 1 holds no meaning unless parBackupDirPath is set also

parMigrateOn.name: parMigrateOn
parMigrateOn.description: This variable specifies whether static records in the wins database should be treated as dynamic records during conflicts with new dynamic registrations.

dfDatafilesTable.name: dfDatafilesTable
dfDatafilesTable.description: A list of datafiles specified under the Datafiles key in the registry. These files are used for statically initialization of the WINS database

dfDatafileIndex.name: dfDatafileIndex
dfDatafileIndex.description: Used for indexing entries in the datafiles table. It has no other use

dfDatafileName.name: dfDatafileName
dfDatafileName.description: Name of the datafile to use for static initialization

pullInitTime.name: pullInitTime
pullInitTime.description: This variable indicates whether pull should be done at WINS invocation and at reconfiguration. If any pull group's mib variable is set, that constitutes reconfiguration

pullCommRetryCount.name: pullCommRetryCount
pullCommRetryCount.description: This variable gives the retry count in case of comm failure when doing pull replication. This is the max. number of retries that will be done at the interval specified for the Partner before WINS will stop for a certain number (canned) of replication time intervals before starting again.

pullPnrTable.name: pullPnrTable
pullPnrTable.description: A list of Partners with which pull replication needs to be done

pPullPnrEntry.name: pPullPnrEntry
pPullPnrEntry.description: This is the row corresponding to a partner

pullPnrAdd.name: pullPnrAdd
pullPnrAdd.description: This is the address of the remote WINS partner

pullPnrSpTime.name: pullPnrSpTime
pullPnrSpTime.description: This variable gives the specific time at which pull replication should occur

pullPnrTimeInterval.name: pullPnrTimeInterval
pullPnrTimeInterval.description: This variable gives the time interval for pull replication

pullPnrMemberPrec.name: pullPnrMemberPrec
pullPnrMemberPrec.description: This is the precedence to be given to members of the special group pulled from the WINS. Note: the precedence of locally registered members of a special group is more than any replicas pulled in

pullPnrNoOfSuccRpls.name: pullPnrNoOfSuccRpls
pullPnrNoOfSuccRpls.description: The number of times replication was successful with the WINS after invocation or reset of counters

pullPnrNoOfCommFails.name: pullPnrNoOfCommFails
pullPnrNoOfCommFails.description: The number of times replication was unsuccessful with the WINS due to comm. failure (after invocation or reset of counters

pullPnrVersNoLowWord.name: pullPnrVersNoLowWord
pullPnrVersNoLowWord.description: The low word of the highest vers. no found in records owned by this WINS.

pullPnrVersNoHighWord.name: pullPnrVersNoHighWord
pullPnrVersNoHighWord.description: The high word of the highest vers. no found in records owned by this WINS.

pushInitTime.name: pushInitTime
pushInitTime.description: This variable indicates whether a push (i.e. notification message) should be done at invocation.

pushRplOnAddChg.name: pushRplOnAddChg
pushRplOnAddChg.description: This variable indicates whether a notification message should be sent when address changes

pushPnrTable.name: pushPnrTable
pushPnrTable.description: A list of WINS Partners with which push replication is to be initiated

pushPnrEntry.name: pushPnrEntry
pushPnrEntry.description: This is the row corresponding to the WINS pnr

pushPnrUpdateCount.name: pushPnrUpdateCount
pushPnrUpdateCount.description: This variable indicates the # of updates that should result in a push message

cmdPullTrigger.name: cmdPullTrigger
cmdPullTrigger.description: This variable when set will cause the WINS to pull from the remote WINS identified by the IpAddress

cmdPushTrigger.name: cmdPushTrigger
cmdPushTrigger.description: This variable when set will cause the WINS to push a notification message to the remote WINS identified by the IpAddress

cmdDeleteWins.name: cmdDeleteWins
cmdDeleteWins.description: This variable when set will cause all information pertaining to a WINS (data records, context information to be deleted from the local WINS. Use this only when owner-address mapping table is getting to near capacity. NOTE: deletion of all information pertaining to the managed WINS is not permitted

cmdDoScavenging.name: cmdDoScavenging
cmdDoScavenging.description: This variable when set will cause WINS to do scavenging.

cmdDoStaticInit.name: cmdDoStaticInit
cmdDoStaticInit.description: When set WINS will do static initialization using the file specified as the value. If 0 is specified, WINS will do static initialization using the files specified in the registry (can be read-written using Datafile table

cmdNoOfWrkThds.name: cmdNoOfWrkThds
cmdNoOfWrkThds.description: Sets the number of worker threads in WINS

cmdPriorityClass.name: cmdPriorityClass
cmdPriorityClass.description: Set the priority class of WINS to normal or high

cmdResetCounters.name: cmdResetCounters
cmdResetCounters.description: Reset the counters. Value is ignored

cmdDeleteDbRecs.name: cmdDeleteDbRecs
cmdDeleteDbRecs.description: This variable when set will cause all date records pertaining to a WINS to be deleted from the local WINS. Note: Only data records are deleted.

cmdDRPopulateTable.name: cmdDRPopulateTable
cmdDRPopulateTable.description: This variable can set to retrieve records of a WINS whose Ip address is provided. When set the table is populated right-away

cmdDRDataRecordsTable.name: cmdDRDataRecordsTable
cmdDRDataRecordsTable.description: This is the table that stores the data records The records are sorted lexicographically by name Note: the table is cached (to save on overhead on WINS) To repopulate the table, set cmdDRDataRecordsTable mib var

cmdDRRecordEntry.name: cmdDRRecordEntry
cmdDRRecordEntry.description: data record owned by WINS whose address was specified when CmdDRRecordsTable was set

cmdDRRecordAddress.name: cmdDRRecordAddress
cmdDRRecordAddress.description: Address(es) of the record. If the record is a multihomed record or a special group, the addresses are returned sequentially in pairs. Each pair is comprised of the address of the owner wins followed by the address of the machine (multihomed)/member (special group). Note: Following snmp's convention, the records are always returned in network byte order

cmdWinsVersNoLowWord.name: cmdWinsVersNoLowWord
cmdWinsVersNoLowWord.description: The low word of the version number counter of the WINS

cmdWinsVersNoHighWord.name: cmdWinsVersNoHighWord
cmdWinsVersNoHighWord.description: The high word of the version number counter of the WINS
